The Deoksu Jang clan (Korean: 덕수 장씨; Hanja: 德水 張氏) is one of the bon-gwan or Korean clans from Kaepung County, North Hwanghae Province.The clan was founded by Jang Sun Ryong, an Arab-Uiguric Muslim civil servant who served in the Goryeo court.
According to the research held in 2015, the clan has 24,185 members.

Origin
Jang Sun Ryong entered Goryeo as a fatherly master of Princess Jeguk, daughter of Kublai Khan, who was married off to Chungnyeol of Goryeo.

